";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Jaime Marchwinski";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2538:"<p>Howdy all! We&#8217;re releasing a quick update here that improves the appearance of maps and map view, and adds a recurrence rule for multi-day events.</p>
<p>This is a minor release that should be smooth sailing when updating. That said, it&#8217;s always a good idea to <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-site-backups/">backup</a> your site and test changes in a <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/">development environment</a> before installing this on your live site, as you would with any other WordPress update.</p>
<hr />
<p>Let&#8217;s get to the changelogs:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Version</strong> &#8211; Events Calendar PRO 5.0.1 is only compatible with The Events Calendar 5.0.1 and higher.</li>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; We fixed the width of days and the day selector on the new week view when using the &#8216;hide weekend&#8217; setting.</li>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; We have removed the filter bar on venue and organizer pages for new views.</li>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; This fixes the additional fields blocks dropdown from being covered by the Add Block button in the block editor, which prevented additional fields from saving.</li>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; We now only show the distance to events for new map view if the location is searched.</li>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; We added a fix that prevents refreshing the default map if an event with the same venue as the current event is clicked in the new map view.</li>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; We resolved an issue so that the map does not display on new venue view if enable maps setting is disabled.</li>
<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; We added a recurrence rule that matches the date span of the multiday dates.</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; We removed the find events button and related data when the events bar is disabled.</li>
<li><strong>Hooks</strong> &#8211; <a href="https://docs.theeventscalendar.com/reference/since/events.pro5.0.1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://docs.theeventscalendar.com/reference/since/events.pro5.0.1/</a></li>
<li><strong>Language</strong> &#8211;<kbd>10 new strings added, 69 updated, 0 fuzzied, and 0 obsoleted</kbd></li>
</ul>
